m\": \"the stories\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2582}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gender and race were at the forefront from the start.\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2659, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gender\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2612}, {\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2621}, {\"ngram\": \"the forefront\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2643}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From its inception in 1896, the modern Olympics sought to create a powerful iconography of visual images to deify sport.\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2781, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its inception\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2679}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"a powerful iconography\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2748}, {\"ngram\": \"visual images\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2765}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2780}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opening and closing ceremonies highlighted the spectacle of the Games, while from 1908 until Melbourne in 1956, each summer Games washeralded by a postershowcasing the idealised and generally naked bodies of powerful white men.\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2878, \"end\": 2887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5740171029894591e-12, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Opening and closing ceremonies\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2813}, {\"ngram\": \"the spectacle\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2839}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 2852}, {\"ngram\": \"each summer Games\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2912}, {\"ngram\": \"a postershowcasing\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 2946}, {\"ngram\": \"the idealised and generally naked bodies\", \"from\": 2947, \"to\": 2987}, {\"ngram\": \"powerful white men\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 3009}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) votes to award the 1924 Summer Olympics to Paris, choosing the French capital ahead of Amsterdam, Los Angeles, Prague and Rome.pic.twitter.com/Dvt55sIGkp - 1924 Live (@100YearsAgoLive)June 2, 2021 In 1936 the diminutive brown-haired Hitler brought television to Germany in order to broadcast his fascistic white supremacist vision of dominant tall blond blue-eyed men to the world - only for theAfrican American athlete Jesse Owensto famously disrupt those visions with his four gold medals as the crowd in Berlin chanted his name.\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3018, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3018, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3099, \"end\": 3104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2599229829091537e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3119, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999420431019664, \"rank\": 5.6316155209083325e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://