bsence from the official images used to promote the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4047, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Powerful women\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 3948}, {\"ngram\": \"their absence\", \"from\": 3979, \"to\": 3992}, {\"ngram\": \"the official images\", \"from\": 3998, \"to\": 4017}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4034, \"to\": 4046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, the bodies of strong athletic women have beenmore likely to attract suspicion and censure, than celebration, as the advent of 'sex testing' shows.\", \"from\": 4049, \"to\": 4203, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bodies\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4067}, {\"ngram\": \"strong athletic women\", \"from\": 4071, \"to\": 4092}, {\"ngram\": \"suspicion\", \"from\": 4125, \"to\": 4134}, {\"ngram\": \"censure\", \"from\": 4139, \"to\": 4146}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration\", \"from\": 4153, \"to\": 4164}, {\"ngram\": \"the advent\", \"from\": 4169, \"to\": 4179}, {\"ngram\": \"sex testing' shows\", \"from\": 4184, \"to\": 4202}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ancient Olympics had excluded women, and the founder of the modern Olympics, Pierre de Coubertin, sought to do the same.\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4288, \"end\": 4307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ancient Olympics\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4225}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4244}, {\"ngram\": \"the founder\", \"from\": 4250, \"to\": 4261}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 4265, \"to\": 4284}]}, {\"sentence\": \"De Coubertin was inspired by the British notion that sports could turn boys into good strong men.\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4365, \"end\": 4372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999946060315734, \"rank\": 3.306385445067254e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"De Coubertin\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4342}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4389}, {\"ngram\": \"boys\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4405}, {\"ngram\": \"good strong men\", \"from\": 4411, \"to\": 4426}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Games,\\\" he proclaimed, \\\"are the solemn and periodic exaltation of male sport - with the applause of women as a reward.\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4552, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Games\", \"from\": 4430, \"to\": 4439}, {\"ngram\": \"periodic exaltation\", \"from\": 4477, \"to\": 4496}, {\"ngram\": \"male sport\", \"from\": 4500, \"to\": 4510}, {\"ngram\": \"the applause\", \"from\": 4518, \"to\": 4530}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4534, \"to\": 4539}, {\"ngram\": \"a reward\", \"from\": 4543, \"to\": 4551}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"An Olympiad with females would be impractical, uninteresting, unaesthetic and improper.\\\"\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4643, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An Olympiad\", \"from\": 4555, \"to\": 4566}, {\"ngram\": \"females\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) hasrecently sought to defend de Coubertin, arguing that he was just trying to protect women from prurient spectators.\", \"from\": 4645, \"to\": 4804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4651, \"end\": 4688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4651, \"end\": 4688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"de Coubertin\", \"from\": 4716, \"to\": 4728}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4773, \"to\": 4778}, {\"ngram\": \"prurient spectators\", \"from\": 4784, \"to\": 4803}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, protecting women from themselves wasone of the main rationales used to exclude them from sport.\", \"from\": 4806, \"to\": 4910, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4831}, {\"ngram\": \"the main rationales\", \"from\": 4858, \"to\": 4877}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 4909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's bodies were too weak, too frail.\", \"from\": 4911, \"to\": 4951, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women's bodies\", \"from\": 4911, \"to\": 4925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletics was too dangerous, especially when it came to contact sports.\", \"from\": 4952, \"to\": 5023, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletics\", \"from\": 4952, \"to\": 4961}, {\"ngram\": \"contact sports\", \"from\": 5008, \"to\": 5022}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inclusion had to be fought for at every turn, despite countless Olympics revealing that the belief that there is no mass audience for women's sport is, in fact, nonsense.\", \"from\": 5025, \"to\": 5195, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Inclusion\", \"from\": 5025, \"to\": 5034}, {\"ngram\": \"every turn\", \"from\": 5059, \"to\": 5069}, {\"ngram\": \"countless Olympics\", \"from\": 5079, \"to\": 5097}, {\"ngram\": \"the belief\", \"from\": 5113, \"to\": 5123}, {\"ngram\": \"no mass audience\", \"from\": 5138, \"to\": 5154}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sport\", \"from\": 5159, \"to\": 5172}, {\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 5180, \"to\": 5184}, {\"ngram\": \"nonsense\", \"from\": 5186, \"to\": 5194}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A rival Olympiad for women in the 1920s spurred the IOC to reluctant concessions around athletics, but from 1928 to 1960 the percentage of female competitors only increased from 10 percent to 11 percent.\", \"from\": 5197, \"to\": 5400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5251, \"end\": 5254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1601572605634516e-48, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A rival Olympiad\", \"from\": 5197, \"to\": 5213}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5218, \"to\": 5223}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1920s\", \"from\": 5227, \"to\": 5236}, {\"ngram\": \"reluctant concessions\", \"from\": 5256, \"to\": 5277}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 5285, \"to\": 5294}, {\"ngram\": \"the percentage\", \"from\": 5318, \"to\": 5332}, {\"ngram\": \"female competitors\", \"from\": 5336, \"to\": 5354}, {\"ngram\": \"10 percent\", \"from\": 5375, \"to\": 5385}, {\"ngram\": \"11 percent\", \"from\": 5389, \"to\": 5399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a woman running the original modern Olympics marathon course in 1896, it took until 1984 for women to be 'allowed' to compete in this event at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5402, \"to\": 5566, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a woman\", \"from\": 5410, \"to\": 5417}, {\"ngram\": \"the original modern Olympics marathon course\", \"from\": 5426, \"to\": 5470}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5503, \"to\": 5508}, {\"ngram\": \"this event\", \"from\": 5539, \"to\": 5549}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5565}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And even in 2024, when women make up half of the athletes at the Games, the length of the cycling road race for women (157.6km) was more than 100km shorter than for the men (272km).\", \"from\": 5568, \"to\": 5749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5591, \"to\": 5596}, {\"ngram\": \"half\", \"from\": 5605, \"to\": 5609}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 5613, \"to\": 5625}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 5629, \"to\": 5638}, {\"ngram\": \"the length\", \"from\": 5640, \"to\": 5650}, {\"ngram\": \"the cycling road race\", \"from\": 5654, \"to\": 5675}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5680, \"to\": 5685}, {\"ngram\": \"157.6km\", \"from\": 5687, \"to\": 5694}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 5733, \"to\": 5740}, {\"ngram\": \"272km\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nevertheless, women were at the centre of the glorious photographs created from the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 5751, \"to\": 5849, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5765, \"to\": 5770}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 5779, \"to\": 5789}, {\"ngram\": \"the glorious photographs\", \"from\": 5793, \"to\": 5817}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 5831, \"to\": 5848}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it was the images of one female athlete that gained the most attention: Algerian gold medal boxer Imane Khelif.\", \"from\": 5851, \"to\": 5966, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the images\", \"from\": 5862, \"to\": 5872}, {\"ngram\": \"one female athlete\", \"from\": 5876, \"to\": 5894}, {\"ngram\": \"the most attention\", \"from\": 5907, \"to\": 5925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the guise of protecting women, Khelif waswilfully misgendered as a manwho threatened the safety of the women she was fighting.\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 6097, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the guise\", \"from\": 5971, \"to\": 5980}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5995, \"to\": 6000}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 6002, \"to\": 6008}, {\"ngram\": \"a manwho\", \"from\": 6036, \"to\": 6044}, {\"ngram\": \"the safety\", \"from\": 6056, \"to\": 6066}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\", \"from\": 6070, \"to\": 6079}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is no accident that the celebrities leading these disingenuous charges turned to visual images as if they provided proof of their claims.\", \"from\": 6099, \"to\": 6239, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no accident\", \"from\": 6105, \"to\": 6116}, {\"ngram\": \"the celebrities\", \"from\": 6122, \"to\": 6137}, {\"ngram\": \"these disingenuous charges\", \"from\": 6146, \"to\": 6172}, {\"ngram\": \"visual images\", \"from\": 6183, \"to\": 6196}, {\"ngram\": \"proof\", \"from\": 6217, \"to\": 6222}, {\"ngram\": \"their claims\", \"from\": 6226, \"to\": 6238}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not only are pictures supposed to tell a thousand words, they arealso supposed to convey the truth.\", \"from\": 6241, \"to\": 6340, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a thousand words\", \"from\": 6280, \"to\": 6296}, {\"ngram\": \"the truth\", \"from\": 6330, \"to\": 6339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Especially when it comes to notoriously slippery notions of gender, sex, and race.\", \"from\": 6341, \"to\": 6423, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"notoriously slippery notions\", \"from\": 6369, \"to\": 6397}, {\"ngram\": \"gender\", \"from\": 6401, \"to\": 6407}, {\"ngram\": \"sex\", \"from\": 6409, \"to\": 6412}, {\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 6418, \"to\": 6422}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, over the last few years,pictures of athletes like Hannah Mouncey and Lia Thomashave been used by anti-trans activists to represent trans women as monstrous threats to cis women.\", \"from\": 6425, \"to\": 6607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6482, \"end\": 6496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mouncey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hannah Mouncey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13365117\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mouncey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mouncey\"}, {\"begin\": 6563, \"end\": 6574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"score\": 0.7896221521117759, \"rank\": 0.2664285029560523, \"text\": \"trans women\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last few years\", \"from\": 6435, \"to\": 6453}, {\"ngram\": \"pictures\", \"from\": 6454, \"to\": 6462}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6466, \"to\": 6474}, {\"ngram\": \"Lia Thomashave\", \"from\": 6499, \"to\": 6513}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-trans activists\", \"from\": 6527, \"to\": 6547}, {\"ngram\": \"monstrous threats\", \"from\": 6576, \"to\": 6593}, {\"ngram\": \"cis women\", \"from\": 6597, \"to\": 6606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet these images draw on longstanding fears of powerful women that have been used to limit the participation of many cis girls and women in sports.\", \"from\": 6609, \"to\": 6756, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these images\", \"from\": 6613, \"to\": 6625}, {\"ngram\": \"longstanding fears\", \"from\": 6634, \"to\": 6652}, {\"ngram\": \"powerful women\", \"from\": 6656, \"to\": 6670}, {\"ngram\": \"the participation\", \"from\": 6700, \"to\": 6717}, {\"ngram\": \"many cis girls\", \"from\": 6721, \"to\": 6735}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 6740, \"to\": 6745}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 6749, \"to\": 6755}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Martina Navratilova and Serena Williams, for example,were regularly vilified as monstrous through the use of pictures and cartoons, as if their dominant strength was unnatural and a threat to the safety of other women.\", \"from\": 6758, \"to\": 6976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6760, \"end\": 